    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Material consisting of fragmented particles of mostly siliceous rock, specifically as it appears on the surface of a beach or a desert. Individual particles may range in diameter from approximately 0.0008-0.08 inch. Most rock-forming minerals at the Earth's surface may be constituents of sand, but a limited number are common. Quartz is most common.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
